Fix OOB Write with invalid tile extents (CVE-2026-25990)

Pillow before 12.1.1 has an out-of-bounds write vulnerability triggered by
specially crafted PSD images with negative tile offsets. This adds bounds
checks for negative xoff/yoff values in the decoder and encoder _setimage
functions.

Upstream fix: https://github.com/python-pillow/Pillow/commit/9000313cc5d4a31bdcdd6d7f0781101abab553aa

